      "message": "I think the corruption should be very specific for this to be an issue.\n\nThe code processes SFLV tuples. So to get the issue we need every L small enough to get many records. And in every message we need to have F with some unknown value.\n\nSo in this regard this case becomes no different from JSON with many BejBytestring/BejChoice/BejResourceLink records, where the current code simply prints:\n```No BejBytestring/BejChoice/BejResourceLink support```\n\nSo if we would want to introduce some debug flag / rate limit, we should probably do it general in libbej, including the print mentioned above. With this in mind I think this is a completely separate change and shouldn\u0027 be covered in this patchset",
